## 7. Current System State

The system is currently in a bootstrap phase:

* Governance is active
* Voting is functional
* Executors are deployed
* Initial proposal lifecycle has been tested

Temporary condition:

* DAO currently has unrestricted execution (“Any Action”)

---

## 8. Planned Upgrades

### 8.1 Permission Lockdown

The DAO will transition to:

* Executor-only execution
* Removal of arbitrary contract access
* Strict permission boundaries

---

### 8.2 Registration System

A registration contract will:

* Verify participants
* Mint LABRV automatically
* Gate governance access

---

### 8.3 Full Decentralization

Control will shift from bootstrap configuration to:

* Fully governed system
* No centralized administrative control
* All upgrades executed via DAO

---

## 9. Security Model

LaborCoin prioritizes structural security:

* Restricted execution via executors
* Non-transferable voting power
* High voting thresholds
* Transparent on-chain actions

Risk is reduced by limiting what governance can do, not by trusting participants.

---

## 10. Use Cases

* Strike funding and support
* Collective bargaining coordination
* Resource distribution
* Community-driven initiatives

---

## 11. Limitations

* Early-stage system (bootstrap phase)
* Registration system not yet deployed
* User experience dependent on external interfaces

---

## 12. Conclusion

LaborCoin represents a shift from speculative crypto systems toward functional governance infrastructure.

By combining equalized voting, controlled execution, and transparent decision-making, it provides a foundation for scalable collective action.

